00:03:38.170 --> 00:03:42.760
A little quick terminology,
WCAG is the Web Content

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:45.230
Accessibility Guidelines
and these are maintained

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:49.640
by the World Wide Web
Consortium or W3C.

00:03:49.640 --> 00:03:52.970
I will use WCAG many times
in this presentation.

00:03:54.840 --> 00:03:56.620
Accessibility ready.

00:03:56.620 --> 00:04:02.190
This is a specific tag used in
the WordPress theme repository.

00:04:02.190 --> 00:04:06.240
And it basically means,
meets some guidelines.

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:09.570
And we'll get into exactly which
ones it does, and does not meet.

00:04:10.660 --> 00:04:15.550
And then A11Y, which is an
abbreviation for accessibility.

00:04:15.550 --> 00:04:18.000
If I remember correctly,
it came out of Twitter

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.740
where they were trying to squeeze
everything into 150 characters.

00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:24.560
And so a lot of words
were getting abbreviated.

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:28.490
It removes 11 characters
between A and Y.

00:04:28.490 --> 00:04:32.410
And I also love it because it's
frequently pronounced ally or ally,

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:37.000
which means a friend
of or an associate of.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:41.670
And I like to try and be a friend
to people with various disabilities.

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:47.550
Slides and links are available,
and I will have this link

00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:49.780
on like the first
seven or eight slides.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:56.080
What theme accessibility
is, and is not.

00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:01.860
Your theme is basically
your foundation.

00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:05.450
And you can either start
out with a good foundation,

00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:08.720
or you can end up fighting
yourself and having

00:05:08.720 --> 00:05:12.850
all these different barriers
to deal with over time.

00:05:12.850 --> 00:05:17.020
And I would prefer to start
with a nice good foundation.

00:05:18.170 --> 00:05:22.270
But theme accessibility is
not actually comprehensive.

00:05:23.480 --> 00:05:26.270
It can not do absolutely
everything for you.

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:30.460
A lot of accessibility is
in how you add your content,

00:05:30.460 --> 00:05:32.630
and of course in
the various plug-ins

00:05:32.630 --> 00:05:35.120
and additional functionality
you add to a website.

00:05:39.910 --> 00:05:43.790
An important thing to remember
when talking about plug-ins,

00:05:43.790 --> 00:05:47.720
and page builders and even
Gutenberg itself, is that many

00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:52.940
of these have accessibility issues
and it's important to check into

00:05:52.940 --> 00:05:59.310
what you are using before you
actually use it, and of course test.

00:05:59.310 --> 00:06:01.950
And we're going to do a ton
of hands-on testing in this,

00:06:01.950 --> 00:06:05.160
so it's hopefully going to be
really helpful in getting you going

00:06:05.160 --> 00:06:06.320
on testing your own stuff.

