00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:52.740
So the first one is
Keyboard Navigation.

00:07:53.750 --> 00:07:58.780
Can someone who does not use
a mouse navigate your website?

00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:01.290
Well, as I look at my desk,
I do not even have a mouse.

00:08:01.290 --> 00:08:02.470
I do not use one.

00:08:02.470 --> 00:08:04.700
It actually bothers my
hand to use a mouse.

00:08:04.700 --> 00:08:10.080
So I actually sit here with this
pen on a big wake-up tablet.

00:08:10.080 --> 00:08:15.080
So I already get some benefits
and I do actually use a little bit

00:08:15.080 --> 00:08:18.660
of screen navigation sometimes.

00:08:19.790 --> 00:08:22.340
One of the first things I'll
actually check before I even get

00:08:22.340 --> 00:08:26.470
into keyboard now is I will
do a quick lighthouse test.

00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:29.080
So here we have the
Kaya demo website,

00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.820
and I have imported
the demo content.

00:08:31.820 --> 00:08:36.150
I have configured just
a couple of widgets.

00:08:36.150 --> 00:08:38.550
So I've configured
some footer widgets.

00:08:38.550 --> 00:08:42.380
Just a couple of things are
configured very, very little.

00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:45.710
And I have done the exact
same on the Divi install.

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:51.890
Again, I've configured some
widgets, but otherwise

00:08:51.890 --> 00:08:53.670
I have not configured options.

00:08:56.670 --> 00:09:01.170
So here we can see out of
the box the Divi has a 79.

00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:05.950
Now Lighthouse has a
more limited set of tests

00:09:05.950 --> 00:09:08.980
than some of the other
tools such as AX or WAV.

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:15.520
So the fact that they are
already scoring 79 as a lot

00:09:15.520 --> 00:09:16.910
of things have not passed.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:21.130
So here we can see
this includes a form.

00:09:21.130 --> 00:09:22.790
This is the search form.

00:09:22.790 --> 00:09:25.040
And we can see that
it's missing labels.

00:09:26.430 --> 00:09:29.930
Links don't have a discernible
name, not a great thing.

00:09:31.290 --> 00:09:34.740
The user scalable has been
set to know, which means

00:09:34.740 --> 00:09:39.990
that there is a limit to how
much this website can be zoomed.

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:42.930
This is a problem for
people with poor vision

00:09:42.930 --> 00:09:46.370
as some of them do
a ton of zooming.

00:09:46.370 --> 00:09:49.480
I know people who literally
zoomed to over 1000%.

00:09:55.600 --> 00:10:01.640
Now contrast issues are not
typically a huge issue in themes,

00:10:01.640 --> 00:10:06.360
as many themes allow you to actually
set your own color palettes.

00:10:06.360 --> 00:10:10.630
But for the accessibility ready
tag, it does require that all

00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:17.020
of the contrast by
default meet the 4.5 to 1.

00:10:20.290 --> 00:10:23.980
And of course, this is an
issue with heading elements are

00:10:23.980 --> 00:10:25.240
in non-sequential order.

00:10:25.240 --> 00:10:30.250
That means that by default this
theme has done specific coding

00:10:30.250 --> 00:10:36.560
to typically make elements such as
the sidebar out of order on headings.

00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:40.520
That is really not a great start
because that typically requires

00:10:40.520 --> 00:10:42.500
a lot of code to overwrite that.

00:10:47.530 --> 00:10:49.460
As you can see, I added fine.

00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:51.390
So now we are going
to take it over to AX.

00:10:52.650 --> 00:10:58.920
And in the AX, I am just going to
scan all of my page and it says,

00:10:58.920 --> 00:11:01.000
no automatic issues.

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:04.550
So basically that means that on
their tests, there were no problems.

00:11:06.210 --> 00:11:08.930
Now these tests are
not all encompassing,

00:11:08.930 --> 00:11:10.310
but they are a pretty
good foundation.

00:11:11.410 --> 00:11:13.260
And we'll run the same here.

00:11:13.260 --> 00:11:16.030
We had 30 automatic issues.

00:11:16.030 --> 00:11:20.460
And one of the things I like about
AX is that it does categorize issues.

00:11:20.460 --> 00:11:22.740
Critical, serious,
moderate, and minor.

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:25.770
Well, critical is not great.

00:11:28.070 --> 00:11:31.200
Form elements are missing
labels again,here.

00:11:31.200 --> 00:11:36.230
This is an intentional decision
by Divi to explicitly hide

00:11:36.230 --> 00:11:38.820
from everyone the label
on the search field.

00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:43.010
Zooming and scaling
are not to be disabled.

00:11:43.010 --> 00:11:46.980
Again, they intentionally
disabled the ability

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:48.610
to zoom beyond a certain threshold.

00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:53.410
The color contrast,
I am not too worried about.

00:11:53.410 --> 00:11:54.820
The links are an issue.

00:11:56.860 --> 00:12:00.610
The ID value is not
always an issue.

00:12:00.610 --> 00:12:02.900
That's why it's categorized
here in Axis minor.

00:12:06.680 --> 00:12:09.910
So we will now get on
to the keyboard test.

00:12:09.910 --> 00:12:15.610
Put your cursor in the URL bar,
and then on your keyboard, hit Tab.

00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:20.540
And absolutely nothing happened.

00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:24.090
This is not a good start.

00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:32.090
I'm repeatedly hitting Tab and
absolutely nothing is happening.

00:12:35.470 --> 00:12:41.700
So basically someone using a keyboard
cannot navigate this site whatsoever

00:12:41.700 --> 00:12:44.190
because I can not see anything.

00:12:45.900 --> 00:12:46.900
So that is not good.

00:12:48.770 --> 00:12:51.760
Here I immediately get
a skip to content link.

00:12:51.760 --> 00:12:52.450
That is great.

00:12:52.450 --> 00:12:55.530
That means that if I want
to skip over the menu bar

00:12:55.530 --> 00:12:57.440
and go straight into the
content, I can.

00:13:00.140 --> 00:13:04.310
But I am going to go through...
Here we have a double outline

00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:10.190
on the focus state, which means
that we have a dark gray background,

00:13:10.190 --> 00:13:14.340
and it has both a blue
and a white outline.

00:13:14.340 --> 00:13:16.440
So we can clearly see
that white outline.

00:13:20.080 --> 00:13:25.930
The search is highlighted
with a blue border.

00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:28.880
The button gets a blue
and white outline.

00:13:28.880 --> 00:13:34.040
As we move through the menu,
these are clearly getting focused.

00:13:35.160 --> 00:13:38.280
We can make it through
all of the menus.

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:42.500
Now, would it be slightly more
ideal if we could use arrow keys

00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:47.280
to manage some of those menus and get
out of some of those deeper menus?

00:13:47.280 --> 00:13:48.300
Yes.

00:13:48.300 --> 00:13:52.550
I generally recommend using
the Max Mega Menu plug-in,

00:13:52.550 --> 00:13:56.890
as that has done pretty
good job of improving menus.

00:13:59.260 --> 00:14:01.230
So let's take a look
at the next item.

00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:04.620
Controls.

00:14:04.620 --> 00:14:07.250
So basically this means that
elements that are a button

00:14:07.250 --> 00:14:09.921
and elements that are
input and elements

00:14:09.922 --> 00:14:12.940
that are an anchor must behave
as they are supposed to.

00:14:14.590 --> 00:14:18.220
Essentially this means Divs
and spans are not buttons

00:14:19.690 --> 00:14:23.270
and they should not be
used by the theme as them.

00:14:23.270 --> 00:14:27.920
Most themes do not actually
create too many issues.

00:14:27.920 --> 00:14:32.130
The biggest one would be
typically menu toggles.

00:14:32.130 --> 00:14:35.817
Now as we have seen
this Divi theme is

00:14:35.818 --> 00:14:39.220
already creating a lot of problems.

00:14:39.220 --> 00:14:42.420
So it is going to be
very hard to even test

00:14:42.420 --> 00:14:46.640
whether or not it has any
issues with the keyboard.

00:14:50.960 --> 00:14:52.690
Next we have Skip Links.

00:14:56.070 --> 00:14:58.850
And who do the skip links benefit?

00:14:58.850 --> 00:15:01.920
The skip link is that very first
link that I showed you here

00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:04.420
at the top,
and it says skip to content.

00:15:04.420 --> 00:15:09.350
This allows people using a keyboard
to skip your entire header area

00:15:09.350 --> 00:15:12.900
and main menu and go straight
to your main content.

00:15:12.900 --> 00:15:16.260
This is a really handy thing
for people who use keyboards.

00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:21.060
Obviously the Divi
theme did not have that.

00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:27.460
Forms; for these form guidelines,
it basically is looking

00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:30.650
for a label element
must be visible.

00:15:30.650 --> 00:15:37.010
Here we can see that on the Divi
theme, there is a label element

00:15:37.010 --> 00:15:40.150
that is included by WordPress core.

00:15:40.150 --> 00:15:44.990
However, they have chosen to put a
display none, which hides this label

00:15:44.990 --> 00:15:45.990
from everyone.

00:15:50.030 --> 00:15:53.790
Here you can see on the Kaya theme,
that the label is right there.

00:15:57.030 --> 00:15:59.930
Headings; using
correct heading order.

00:16:01.170 --> 00:16:06.190
So in this case, we will take a
look at these headings down here

00:16:06.190 --> 00:16:07.200
in the footer.

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:10.640
And what you will see is
that this heading is an H3,

00:16:10.640 --> 00:16:14.170
and there is a screen reader
heading that is an H2.

00:16:14.170 --> 00:16:19.870
So we have here on the page your H1,
then we have the screen reader level

00:16:19.870 --> 00:16:21.150
for a footer.

00:16:21.150 --> 00:16:22.840
What a lot of people with
screen readers do is,

00:16:22.840 --> 00:16:25.610
they can actually navigate
the website by getting a list

00:16:25.610 --> 00:16:27.040
of all the headings.

00:16:27.040 --> 00:16:31.280
So putting this footer heading
here, as a screen reader

00:16:31.280 --> 00:16:34.590
heading allows them to immediately
jump straight to footer.

00:16:36.340 --> 00:16:40.780
And then within the footer,
you want things labeled as an H3

00:16:40.780 --> 00:16:41.780
and appropriate.

00:16:45.370 --> 00:16:51.550
Here on Divi, you can take a
look, and it has labeled.

00:16:52.630 --> 00:16:56.020
We have these H3s,
but there's no H2s.

00:16:57.910 --> 00:17:04.650
Now, these headings are sometimes
setable, depending on what type

00:17:04.650 --> 00:17:05.650
of heading they are.

